data.description: Price reduced 10K.  Your search is over.  This home is it, offering 4 BR, 3.5 baths with added finished rooms in the lower level that could be used for hobby rooms, additional bedrooms or guest/in-law suite potential.  This lovely home offers lrg kitchen w/ island, granite counters, ss appliances and huge pantry closet.  The breakfast/dining bump out and lrg living room are both off the kitchen with an open floor plan and offering sliding doors from the dining area to lrg deck, featuring trex decking to enjoy BBQ'S & evening sunsets.  Deck also features stairs to the lower-level wrap around tumble stone/hardscaped patio, which is ideal for extended entertaining.  There's a main level  lrg office/den/formal dining room off the front foyer w/ double doors for added privacy.   Also on the main level is a small mud room just inside from the 2-car front loading integral garage. Upstairs is a huge primary suite w/ primary bath and massive walk-in closet, 3 additional bedrooms, a 2nd full bath and the 2nd floor laundry rm.  The lower level is fully finished except for the utility closet.  There's a very large family rm / recreation rm and 2 add'l rooms to use for whatever you may need (den, exercise rm, study, hobby, craft rm storage or more) featuring luxury vinyl plank flooring throughout the whole LL.  Double atrium doors to the patio.  Lower-level fin sq ft is estimated.  Total sq ft is 3,389.  The total fin sq ft is approx. 3,317.   This is a nice large home on a quarter acre lot.    This home is located in the sought after Boonsboro School District in the quaint town of Keedysville,  just a few miles to the Antietam Battlefields, the C & O Canal, the Potomac River, The Appalachian Trail, The Washington County Agricultural & Education Center.  Only 3.7 mi to Boonsboro, 3.6 mi to Sharpsburg, 7.6 mi to Shepherdstown, WV, 13.7 mi to Hagerstown, 20 mi to Frederick, 34.5 to Leesburg, VA, 66 mi to Washington DC, 68 mi to Baltimore and so much more.
